     1в†’# The only accessible & unstyled & full featured Input OTP component in the Web.
     3в†’### OTP Input for React рџ”ђ by [@guilhermerodz](https://twitter.com/guilherme_rodz)
    18в†’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/753751f5-eda8-4145-a4b9-7ef51ca5e453
    19в†’
    20в†’## Usage
    22в†’```bash
    23в†’npm install input-otp
    24в†’```
    25в†’
    26в†’Then import the component.
    27в†’
    28в†’```diff
      в†’вЂ¦
    39в†’## Default example
    41в†’The example below uses `tailwindcss` `@shadcn/ui` `tailwind-merge` `clsx`:
    42в†’
    43в†’```tsx
    44в†’'use client'
    45в†’import { OTPInput, SlotProps } from 'input-otp'
    46в†’<OTPInput
    47в†’  maxLength={6}
      в†’вЂ¦
   136в†’## How it works
   138в†’There's currently no native OTP/2FA/MFA input in HTML, which means people are either going with 1. a simple input design or 2. custom designs like this one.
   139в†’This library works by rendering an invisible input as a sibling of the slots, contained by a `relative`ly positioned parent (the container root called _OTPInput_).
   140в†’
   141в†’## Features
   143в†’This is the most complete OTP input on the web. It's fully featured 
   144в†’
   145в†’<details>
   146в†’<summary>Supports iOS + Android copy-paste-cut</summary>
   147в†’
   148в†’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bdbdc96a-23da-4e89-bff8-990e6a1c4c23
   149в†’
      в†’вЂ¦
   198в†’### Auto tracks if the input has space in the right side for the badge
   200в†’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bf01af88-1f82-463e-adf4-54a737a92f59
   201в†’
   202в†’</details>
   203в†’
   204в†’## API Reference
   206в†’### OTPInput
   208в†’The root container. Define settings for the input via props. Then, use the `render` prop to create the slots.
   209в†’
   210в†’#### Props
   212в†’```ts
   213в†’type OTPInputProps = {
   214в†’  // The number of slots
   215в†’  maxLength: number
   216в†’
   217в†’  // Render function creating the slots
   218в†’  render: (props: RenderProps) => React.ReactElement
      в†’вЂ¦
